description.narrative: UNICEF promoted behavior and social changes in nutritional, hygiene, sanitation and COVID-19 practices among vulnerable communities. UNICEF successfully contributed to decreased harmful sanitation practices (open defecation) in Angola while raising the profile of hand hygiene to prevent the spread of COVID-19. User trust in healthcare providers and consequent healthcare seeking during COVID times have increased. An observed high demand for and uptake of COVID-19 vaccination, together with adoption of promoted preventive practices contributed to declines in cases. Demand for birth registration rose after parents received integrated SMS reminder messages on vaccination and birth registration. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:06/01/2022
